    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ḱynʒ" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ḱynʒ</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kinʒæ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>невестка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>daughter-in-law</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>невеста</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>bride</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>кукла</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>doll</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>ḱynʒʒon ḱyzg</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>девушка на выданье</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>a girl ready for marriage</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ḱynʒxæssæg</orth><form
                                type="variant"><orth>ḱynʒxon</orth></form></form>
                        <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kinʒxon</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>свадебный дружка</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>groomsman</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ḱynʒæxsæv</orth></form>
                        <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kinʒæxsævæ</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>свадьба</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>marriage</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ḱynʒæmbal</orth></form>
                        <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kinʒæmbal</orth></form>
                        <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                    <q>провожатый невесты</q>
                                </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                    <q>bride guide</q>
                                </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                    <q>шафер</q>
                                </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                    <q>bridesman</q>
                                </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ḱynʒy fæcyd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вышла замуж</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>she got married</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>55</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ḱynʒ æmæ siaxsy arǧwanmæ akodtoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>невесту и жениха повели в церковь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the bride and groom were taken to church</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>67</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>aḱynʒ kæninag dy dæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тебя нужно выдать замуж</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>you need to marry</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ḱyzg — ḱynʒʒon, læppū — syvællon, kæræzījæn kʼæjttæ k˳yd
                            wydajkkoj!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>девушка — на выданье, мальчик — ребенок, как они могли быть парой
                                друг другу!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a girl is of marriageable age, a boy is a child, how could they be a
                                couple to each other!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>76</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>bon syn k˳yvdæn wydī, xsæv ta ḱynʒæxsævæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>день был им для пиршества, ночь — для свадьбы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they have a day to feast, a night for the wedding</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."
                            /><biblScope>103</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>adæmæn sæ ḱynʒxonty qazt xæxtæ, kʼæʒæxtæ xæssy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>у людей свадебная пляска сотрясает горы и скалы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>people's wedding dance shakes mountains and rocks</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>25</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">— В дигорском в значении ‘невестка’ обычно <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_nostæ"/>.</note>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">— In Digor the meaning ‘daughter-in-law’ is
                    usually conveyed by <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nostæ"/>.</note>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. %i*kantī-%i (%ikan%i + %iti%i). Для основы
                    %ikan-%i в значении ‘молодой’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kanā-, kanya-</w>
                        <gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>молодая женщина</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>kanistha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>младший</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kainī-, kainyā-,</w></mentioned>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīz</w>
                        <gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kīna</w>
                        <gloss><q>дочь</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Оформление %i-tī%i характерно для
                    восточноиранских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>kōnd, kənd</w>
                        <gloss><q>женщина</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>жена</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w>kənd
                            yund-</w>
                        <gloss><q>жениться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                            ><w>be-kənd</w>
                        <gloss><q>вдовец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                            ><w>vrit-kənd</w>
                        <gloss><q>жена брата</q></gloss></mentioned> (? <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                    547</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kintika</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>150</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>knc</w>
                        <gloss><q>девушка</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>247</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kant-(knt-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>род по женской линии</q></gloss></mentioned>
                            (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JA"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1951, стр. 113—114</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">1951, pp. 113—114</biblScope></bibl>). Ср. также
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>-k’in</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в %it’ik’in%i (из
                            %i*pati-kin%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>госпожа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>знатная дама</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ЗВО"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">V 286
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">V 286 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). —
                    Слово распознается в аланских фразах, записанных %sЦецом%s, в форме %iκιντζ%i
                    ‘женщина’. Звуковая история ясна: %ikinʒ-%i из %i*kantī-%i, как <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7lxyncʼ" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><w>lxincʼ</w></ref> ‘узел’ из %i*granthi-%i. — Ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kʼannæg"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                            478</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Фрейман,
                            Rocznik orient. 1927, стр. 163</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en"
                            >Freiman, Rocznik orient. 1927, p. 163</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                        /><biblScope>21-22</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>43, 119, 258,
                    316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian %i*kantī-%i (%ikan%i + %iti%i). For
                    the stem %ikan-%i in the meaning ‘young’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kanā-, kanya-</w>
                        <gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>young woman</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>kanistha-</w>
                        <gloss><q>the youngest</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kainī-, kainyā-,</w></mentioned>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kanīz</w>
                        <gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kīna</w>
                        <gloss><q>daughter</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The %i-tī%i marking is typical
                    of East Iranian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>kōnd, kənd</w>
                        <gloss><q>woman</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>wife</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><w>kənd
                            yund-</w>
                        <gloss><q>get married</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                            ><w>be-kənd</w>
                        <gloss><q>widower</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                            ><w>vrit-kənd</w>
                        <gloss><q>brother's wife</q></gloss></mentioned> (? <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                    547</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>kintika</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>150</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>knc</w>
                        <gloss><q>girl</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>247</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kant-(knt-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>female line</q></gloss></mentioned>
                            (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JA"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1951, стр. 113—114</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">1951, pp. 113—114</biblScope></bibl>). Cf. also <mentioned
                        xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>-k’in</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in %it’ik’in%i
                            (from %i*pati-kin%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>mistress</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>lady of high degree</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ЗВО"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">V 286
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">V 286 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). —
                    This word is recognized in Alan phrases recorded by %sTzetzes%s, in the form
                    %iκιντζ%i ‘woman’. The phonetic history is clear: %ikinʒ-%i from %i*kantī-%i, as
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lxyncʼ" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><w>lxincʼ</w></ref> ‘knot’ from %i*granthi-%i. — Cf.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼannæg"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                            478</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Фрейман,
                            Rocznik orient. 1927, стр. 163</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en"
                            >Freiman, Rocznik orient. 1927, p. 163</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                        /><biblScope>21-22</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>43, 119, 258,
                    316</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
        </body>
